- Npgsql
- DotNetEnv


## Base de Datos


### Tabla products

```sql
CREATE TABLE products (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name TEXT NOT NULL,
    normalized_name TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    barcode VARCHAR(32),
    price INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK (price >= 0),
    eco_score INTEGER CHECK (eco_score BETWEEN 0 AND 100),
    social_score INTEGER CHECK (social_score BETWEEN 0 AND 100),
    category TEXT,
    image_url TEXT,
    stock_actual INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    stock_minimo INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at TIMESTAMP,
    is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE
);

CREATE TABLE stock_movements (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES products(id),
    movement_type INTEGER NOT NULL,
    quantity INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK (quantity > 0),
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
    user_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id)
);

CREATE TABLE users (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    username TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    password_hash TEXT NOT NULL,
    role INTEGER NOT NULL,
    is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE TABLE audit_logs (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INTEGER REFERENCES users(id),
    action TEXT NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

git clone https://github.com/tuusuario/miapp.git
cd miapp

DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=miapp
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=tu_password


dotnet restore

dotnet run --project MiApp.UI

Seguridad y Transacciones

El sistema utiliza:

FOR UPDATE para bloqueo de filas

Transacciones SQL

Rollback automático en caso de error

Validación de stock antes de salida

Contraseñas hasheadas

Control de permisos por rol

Ejemplo de bloqueo:

SELECT stock_actual 
FROM products 
WHERE id = @id 
FOR UPDATE;

